## Appendix C Inducing Points

Let \(\bm{z}\in X^{M}\) be a set of \(M>0\) inducing point locations. The variational inducing point framework of Titsias [43; 44] substitutes our observed targets \(\bm{y}\) with the inducing targets \(\bm{u}\in\mathbb{R}^{M}\). Our Gaussian process, conditional on a set of inducing locations and targets, is given by the mean and covariance functions

\[\mu_{f|\bm{u}}(\cdot) =\mathbf{K}_{(\cdot)\bm{z}}\mathbf{K}_{\bm{zz}}^{-1}\bm{u} k_{f|\bm{u}}(\cdot,\cdot^{\prime}) =\mathbf{K}_{(\cdot,\cdot^{\prime})}-\mathbf{K}_{(\cdot)\bm{z}}\mathbf{K}_{\bm {zz}}^{-1}\mathbf{K}_{\bm{zz}(\cdot^{\prime})}.\] (17)

